---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CompletenessChecklist from '../../components/CompletenessChecklist.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="City data intake | CourtScope Admin" noindex={true}><section class="section"><div class="shell"><p class="eyebrow">Admin · Data intake</p><h1>Receive a complete city dataset</h1><p class="lede">This page documents the real repository intake contract. It does not upload files directly from the browser or pretend a provider transfer occurred.</p><div class="notice warning"><strong>Public repository boundary:</strong> Only a complete, de-identified, privacy-reviewed package may enter <code>data/intake/incoming</code>. Raw files containing personal information must remain in approved private storage.</div><h2>Required batch folder</h2><pre class="receipt">data/intake/incoming/&lt;city-slug&gt;/&lt;batch-id&gt;/
├── manifest.json
├── data.csv or data.json
└── data-dictionary.md (or another declared dictionary file)</pre><CompletenessChecklist /><h2>What the workflow does</h2><div class="pipeline"><article><h3>Validate</h3><p>Checks the manifest, columns, records, judge identities, coverage, privacy attestations, and model publication minimums.</p></article><article><h3>Reject safely</h3><p>Moves an incomplete package to the rejection folder and writes a processing receipt. Other valid batches continue.</p></article><article><h3>Publish</h3><p>Creates city judges, cases, release metadata, registry state, and public downloads only when every gate passes.</p></article><article><h3>Retain and clean</h3><p>Moves the accepted input package to processed retention and updates the admin cleanup queue.</p></article></div><div class="actions"><a class="button" href="/admin">Open command center</a><a class="button secondary" href="/add-cities">Public records-request guide</a></div></div></section></BaseLayout>
